trial detention. 
<b><i>Non-governmental sources 2008:</i></b>  It is reported that 
extensive time periods specified for summons, formal 
arrest by the police, approval of the arrest by the 
procuratorate, and special arrangements for some 
categories of suspects remained in force. It is alleged 
that suspects could still be held legally in police 
custody for up to 37 days prior to approval by the 
procuratorate. 
