<p>- On 23 October 2008, the inter-ministerial 
working group issued a report on the 
investigation into the secret CIA-Rendition 
flights in Denmark, Greenland and the Faroe 
Islands. Three journalists complained to the 
Ombudsman about not being granted access 
to information to documents exchanged 
within the working group. On 18 March 
2010, the Ombudsman issued an opinion, 
stating that &#8213;the so-called CIA working 
group, which has investigated the alleged 
CIA-flights in Danish airspace, cannot be 
considered as an independent authority&#8214;, and 
requested reconsideration of the request.  
