The new CPC does not regulate the 
jurisdiction of the investigative bodies 
over investigating the crime. It is now 
regulated under Article 2 of the Decree # 
178 of the Ministry of Justice, dated 29 
September 2010, which is mostly similar 
to what was stated in Art 62 of the old 
CPC.  
However, in practice there are cases, when 
this requirement is not fulfilled. Crimes, 
which might involve responsibility of a 
police officer, to certain extent (most 
important investigative measures are 
conducted), if not fully, is investigated by 
the investigators of Ministry of Interior, 
the same Ministry to which the police 
subordinates. 
 
