total impunity for security 
personnel, especially of the police 
and military, for current as well 
as past violations;  
</p>
<p><b><i>Non-governmental sources</i></b> : In 2009 
there was still widespread impunity for 
members of the security forces 
responsible for serious violations of 
human rights, including torture, 
particularly with regard to atrocities 
committed in East Timor, Papua, Aceh, 
the Malukus and Kalimantan. A number 
</p>
