<p><b><i>Non-governmental sources:</i></b>  No progress has  
been made on this recommendation. 
 
Reportedly, the Charter of Rights permits the detention of 
individuals for psychiatric analysis for an undetermined period, 
without legislating a scheduled time within which the detention 
for such purposes should be reviewed.  This permits and 
legalizes the detention of individuals in circumstances that may 
constitute inhuman and degrading treatment for an indefinite 
period of time. 
