to be held together with adults. The new facility, Metcalfe 
Street Juvenile Remand Centre for boys, which opened in June 
2011, serves the detention of male juveniles only and thus does 
not effectively address the entirety of children being held in 
facilities alongside adults. Despite the opening of the new 
centre, as of 3 September 2011, 28 children remained in police 
lockups. 
It is alleged that female juveniles continue to be routinely 
incarcerated in Fort Augusta and Horizon Remand (adult 
prisons). 
