<b>Government:</b> Under the Jordanian legislation, any 
person who alleges to be a victim of torture, may 
seek a judicial remedy and is entitled to request 
compensation in accordance with article 256 of the 
Civil Law.  
- The Office of Grievances and Human Rights in 
the PSD deals with complaints. Complaints are 
also received through reporting in person to the 
Office or submitting the complaint through official 
and unofficial correspondence. The complaints are 
then investigated, verified and followed up in an 
effective, immediate, comprehensive and impartial 
manner in order to reach a just conclusion.  </p>

