the detainee and stays with him or her 
during the examination.  
 
<b>Government:</b> In February 2010, a joint 
Ministerial order was approved on the 
mandatory participation of forensic experts 
in the conduct of medical examination of 
persons who sustained physical injuries 
while in temporary detention facilities, pre-
trial detention centres and penitentiary 
institutions. 
 
<b><i>Non-governmental sources</i></b> : There have 
been serious shortages of medication in a 
number of penitentiary institutions in 
Karaganda region. Prisoners complained 
about the lack of adequate treatment and 
required medication. 
