which the relatives and representatives of 
the person deprived of their liberty, without 
any exceptions, must be notified from the 
moment of actual deprivation of liberty, is 
pending before the Majlis of the Parliament.  
- On 1 August 2008, the judicial sanctioning 
of arrest was introduced. The person may be 
held in custody for no more 72 hours 
without a court authorization. The 
administration of the temporary detention 
centre is obliged to immediately pass any 
complaint of torture or ill-treatment to the 
public prosecutor.  
