that he gave his statement under physical or 
psychological violence  of the law 
enforcement agencies, he was not informed 
of his right to invite counsel and not to give 
self-incriminatory statements, and his 
interrogation was conducted without 
participation of counsel, the challenged 
statement should be considered as 
inadmissible evidence.&#8214; This is a positive 
</p>
<p>legal rule that should be adopted in the 
Criminal Procedure Code. Moreover, the 
wording of the Code should be more 
explicit and binding by automatically 
recognizing any statement of a suspect or 
accused that was given in the course of the 
pre-trial stages of a criminal case in the 
absence of defence counsel, including 
situations where there was a waiver of 
