</i></b></p>
<p>Reportedly, although the Interim 
Constitution of 2007 states that any act 
of torture shall be punishable by law, 
there is not yet any legal provision that 
declares torture to be a crime in Nepal.  
Reportedly, a draft Penal Code, 
Criminal Procedure Code and 
Sentencing Bill were submitted to the 
parliamentary secretariat in late 
January 2011. However they have yet 
to be circulated among the members of 
parliament. The submission to the 
secretary puts an end to the public </p>

