Bardiya District (report published in December 
2008). 
In Oct. 08, the CPN-M-led Government 
recommended the withdrawal of 349 criminal cases 
(investigations, charges and convictions) of a so-
called &#8213;political nature&#8214;.  They included cases of 
</p>
<p>gross human rights abuses (murder, attempted 
murder and rape), the majority from the conflict 
period. Most cases were against CPN-M members, 
some of whom were senior members of the 
Government at the time, raising concerns about 
ongoing impunity and the de facto provision of 
amnesties.<b>  
 
