<b><i>Non-governmental sources:</i></b>  The 
reported number of child victims of 
violence has steadily increased over the 
past few years and is known to be 
underreported. Corporal punishment, 
while officially banned, is still widely 
used. Studies indicate that 25% of 
children state that they are beaten by 
their own parents, 13% report being 
corporally punished in schools by their 
school teachers.  
