Republic of Moldova ratified the UN 
Convention on the Rights of Persons with 
Disabilities. A strategy for social inclusion of 
persons with disabilities (2010-2013) was 
developed defining the state policy in the field 
of social protection of persons with disabilities 
and its adjustment to international standards and 
provisions of the Convention.  
