<p>(v) Make the declaration 
provided for in article 22 of 
the Convention against 
Torture and Other Cruel, 
Inhuman or Degrading 
Treatment or Punishment 
recognizing the competence 
of the Committee against 
Torture to receive and 
consider communications 
from individuals who claim to 
be victims of a violation of 
the provisions of the 
Convention, as well as to 
ratifying the Optional 
Protocol to the Convention, 
whereby a body shall be set 
up to undertake regular visits 
to all places of detention in 
the country in order to 
prevent torture; invite the 
Working Group on Arbitrary 
Detention and the Special 
Representative of the 
Secretary-General on human 
rights defenders as well as the 
Special Rapporteur on the 
independence of judges and 
lawyers to carry out visits to 
the country. 
